JSE-listed Murray &amp; Roberts (M&amp;R) has sold its steel fabrication subsidiary Genrec to asset management firm Nisela Capital for R185-million. Genrec was the last remaining manufacturing business in the group&rsquo;s portfolio of businesses. M&amp;R on Monday said it believed the sale of Genrec would be in the best interests of the long-term sustainability of the group and its long-term strategy to focus on the global natural resources markets. The transaction is subject to certain conditions precedent and regulatory approvals.